Milkiland’s Directors Want to Reinvest 2010 Profit, IFX Says

-- B y   D a r y n a   K r a s n o l u t s k a
-- 
2011-05-05T16:07:38Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/milkiland-s-directors-want-to-reinvest-2010-profit-ifx-says.html
The board of directors at  Milkiland
NV (MLK) , wants to invest all of last year’s profit in development for
the dairy company, which operates in Russia and Ukraine,
 Interfax   news agency  reported, citing company documents.  The board of directors will suggest to shareholders on June
17 to reinvest 21.99 million euros ($32.1 million) and not to
pay dividends, Interfax said. The board also doesn’t want to put
part of the income into the company’s reserves, according to the
news agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Daryna Krasnolutska in Kiev at 
 dkrasnolutsk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
